    "The tuned iterations of Llama 2 employ supervised fine-tuning (SFT) and reinforcement learning with human feedback (RLHF) techniques.",
    "These methods aim to align the model with human preferences for both helpfulness and safety aspects.",
    "BloomBloom [54] is a multilingual, open-access LLM developed as a collaborative effort by the BigScience project.",
    "Unlike many other large-scale models, Bloom is explicitly designed to support over 46 languages and 13 programming languages, making it one of the most diverse models in terms of linguistic coverage.",
    "Bloom is trained using a transformer architecture with a causal language modeling objective, similar to GPT and OPT, but its extensive multilingual capabilities set it apart."
